pictures.name: Frankfurt Parliament

pictures.content: Iconic picture of the 1848 revolution in Berlin. In the painting one can recongnize in the middle and on the bottom edge the flag of the monarchist Revolutionaries. They wanted a unified Germany with a monarch at its head. On the right side one can see two flags of the republican Revolutionaries. They wanted a Republic based on the French example and therefore constructed their flag with vertical stripes, in the style of the French Tricolor. The orientation of the three colors on the revolutionary German Tricolors varied.
pictures.name: Revolution of 1848 in Berlin

pictures.content: Illustration of the Battle of Laupen (1339) between Swiss forces and an army of the Dukes of Savoy. It still shows the old german red flag with a white cross upon it. The confederate forces are on the right. The Bernese victory at the Battle of Laupen helped bring Bern into the Swiss Confederation.
